# Coding Guidelines

This rule documents the coding standards and conventions used in this project.

## Frontend Code Conventions

### HTML ([index.html](mdc:index.html))
- Use semantic HTML5 elements (section, header, footer, etc.)
- Include descriptive comments for major sections
- Follow BEM naming convention for CSS classes

### CSS ([css/style.css](mdc:css/style.css))
- Organize CSS by component/section
- Use CSS variables for colors and consistent values
- Mobile-first responsive design with media queries
- Use flexbox and grid for layouts

### JavaScript ([js/main.js](mdc:js/main.js))
- Use ES6+ features where appropriate
- Organize code by functionality (data loading, chart init, events)
- Add descriptive comments for complex functions
- Use camelCase for variable and function names

## Backend Code Conventions

### Python ([admin/app.py](mdc:admin/app.py))
- Follow PEP 8 style guidelines
- Use Flask blueprints for larger modules
- Organize routes by functionality
- Include docstrings for functions
- Use descriptive variable names
- Implement proper error handling and logging

## General Guidelines

1. **Security Practices**:
   - Always validate user input
   - Implement proper authentication and authorization
   - Use secure password handling
   - Protect against common web vulnerabilities

2. **Performance**:
   - Optimize image sizes
   - Minimize HTTP requests
   - Use efficient algorithms for data processing
   - Implement pagination for large datasets

3. **Documentation**:
   - Comment complex logic
   - Keep README updated
   - Document API endpoints
   - Include setup instructions
